Decisions cascade into the SDP and into individual ADRs. Each is a one-page decision document in its own right.

| ID | Decision | Sprint deadline | ADR |
|---|---|---|---|
| OAD-1 | Identity and SSO strategy (Azure AD B2C / IdentityServer / Auth0) — and whether tokens issued by CIMS are honoured directly by spokes or whether spokes validate independently against the same identity provider | Sprint 0 | ADR-0003 |
| OAD-2 | Event-bus technology — lightweight built-in (outbox + HTTP webhooks), managed broker (Azure Service Bus, AWS SNS/SQS), or self-hosted (RabbitMQ) | Sprint 0 | [ADR-0012](./decisions/0012-event-bus-technology.md) |
| OAD-3 | Multi-tenancy strategy — separate database per tenant per product, or shared database with tenant ID | Sprint 0 | ADR-0004 |
| OAD-4 | Hosting and data residency — particularly UK-resident storage for HRB projects, and offline-capable handover | Sprint 0 | ADR-0005 |
| OAD-5 | Money handling and multi-currency policy — `decimal(19,4)` confirmed; multi-currency rules to be specified | Sprint 0 | ADR-0006 |
| OAD-6 | HMRC CIS API access strategy — pursue official integration or accept manual verification with audit | Before F5 | ADR-TBC |
| OAD-7 | Open Banking integration for live cash position and automated reconciliation | Before F8 | ADR-TBC |

